<br>
It's a shame to see people all worked up over such a trivial item.<br>
<br>
When information is posted in a PUBLIC forum, and yes - this is a public forum, that information is available to be used.  If this board where perhaps, by invite only - then I could see you getting upset about quotes & pictures.  But that isn't the case.<br>
<br>
I don't think you're pissed off that someone is showing your picture in a location other than the Real Life forum.  I don't think you're pissed off that someone is "quoting" you.  However....<br>
<br>
I DO think you're pissed off because, YOU attempted to "address" <I>(VERY rudely I might add)</I>  a "rumor" in a public forum before confronting Dwarkarn personally.<br>
As such, YOU got called on being a d<!>ickhead.<br>
As such, YOU became the new spotlight of Dwarkarn's humor.  And somehow, I don't think you like to be "picked on".  Perhaps traumatized by some childhood memories?<br>
<br>
While I won't begin to address the supposed "copyright" issues regarding personal pictures, not taken by a 3rd party agency, WILLINGLY posted in a public forum...I will address the "quotes" concern.  <br>
<br>
Ever write a book report or a term paper?  Same principle applies.  Author_X writes a book, "AIM For Dummies".  In my term paper, I quote Author_X.  As long as *I* do not claim said quote as MY original thoughts, statements, what-have-you and I do say that Author_X was responsible for that quote...then there is no plagarism - AKA: No Problem!  Same thing here.  Dwarkarn said YOU were quoted as saying, "XYZ".  Therefore he's free & clear to use your "quotes".<br>
<br>
Now if you really wanted to be anal retentive about it, you could request Dwarkarn to supply a Citations Page. That would be mildly amusing. <p><center>
