<br>
There are all kinds of stories about internet stalking, etc these days.  Sure Lurikeen might not be the ideal target of a stalker, but the point is that when someone posts their RL picture here on this board they should be able to assume that it will not be used elsewhere.<br>
<br>
After all, public or not, that is their picture.  While I don't see a reason someone would want my picture, and I am not sure where my picture is or isn't posted... I would still like to believe that posting on this board I would be safe from people using a picture maliciously.<br>
<br>
People who post their pictures here should not have to worry about what others will do with their pictures.  The whole picture idea came from a sense of community here on the boards.  Sure, people here disagree, but disagreements should stay on this board.  It would suck for people to not be able to post pictures or personal info anymore for fear of what someone else might do with it.<br>
<br>
Anyone who reads these boards regularly knows that I don't agree with Lurikeen often... but I think this is way out of line.<br>
<br>
Lurikeen could probably contact Dwarkarn's host again and let them know that instead of his picture a different picture is being used with his name.  They would probably request it be taken down.  All he would do is host it somewhere else and link to it.<br>
<br>
Lurikeen could inform &quot;Big Brother&quot; that someone is using their name on a web site.  Dwarkarn would just find a different name or way of doing the same thing.<br>
<br>
The reality is that only Dwarkarn can choose to take it down. <p><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~cnjmorris/catcen.jpg>

